wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Pat StrawHi Jessy,Grandpa Bob was a great hunter. I never saw the deer, but I ate pltney of it. I made a lot of meatloaves, but used half hamburg and half venison. Also made slow cooker pot roast with onion soup and Cream of Mushroom soup. Except for the tenderloin, it can be a little chewey, so I would recommend marinating the steaks or getting Adolph's meat tenderizer in the seasoning dept at market. My love is with you as you enjoy your adventures in Wyoming .Memere
